
[1]turkois

   TURK'OIS, n. A mineral, called also calaite, brought from the east; of
   a beautiful light green color, occurring in thin layers, or in rounded
   masses, or in reniform masses, with a botryoidal surface. It is
   susceptible of a high polish,and is used in jewelry. It is usually
   written in the French manner.
